# Generic System Config Dashboard

## Goal Description
Implement a "Generic System Config Dashboard" to manage multiple configuration tables (e.g., KvConfigs, TransporterConfig). This dashboard will allow users to view and edit configurations dynamically based on the selected config type.

## User Review Required
No critical review items identified yet, standard feature addition.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Integration
#### [MODIFY] [config.ts](file:///Users/addhithyarh/Documents/control-center/src/services/config.ts)
- Add `ConfigType` enum (KV_CONFIGS, TRANSPORTER_CONFIG, etc.).
- Add `SystemConfig` interface.
- Add `fetchConfigs(configType: string)` method.
- Add `updateConfig(payload: UpdateConfigPayload)` method.
- Add `supportedTables()` method (if endpoint exists/is needed).

### Frontend Components
#### [NEW] [ConfigManagementPage.tsx](file:///Users/addhithyarh/Documents/control-center/src/modules/config/ConfigManagementPage.tsx)
- Main page component.
- Holds state for `selectedConfigType`, `configs`, `loading`, etc.
- Renders `ConfigTypeSelector` and `ConfigDataGrid`.

#### [NEW] [ConfigTypeSelector.tsx](file:///Users/addhithyarh/Documents/control-center/src/modules/config/ConfigTypeSelector.tsx) (or inline in page)
- Dropdown to select `ConfigTable` type.

#### [NEW] [ConfigDataGrid.tsx](file:///Users/addhithyarh/Documents/control-center/src/modules/config/ConfigDataGrid.tsx) (or inline)
- Table to display config keys, values, descriptions, updated at.
- "Edit" action button.

#### [NEW] [ConfigEditor.tsx](file:///Users/addhithyarh/Documents/control-center/src/modules/config/ConfigEditor.tsx)
- Modal or inline editor.
- Uses a JSON editor (or text area with validation) for the value.

### Routing & Navigation
#### [MODIFY] [navigation.ts](file:///Users/addhithyarh/Documents/control-center/src/config/navigation.ts)
- Add "Config Management" to the "System Config" children.

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///Users/addhithyarh/Documents/control-center/src/App.tsx)
- Add route `/config/management` mapping to `ConfigManagementPage`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run dev` and navigate to the new page.

### Manual Verification
1.  **Navigation**:
    -   Click on "System Config" -> "Config Management" in the sidebar.
    -   Verify the page loads.
2.  **Selection**:
    -   Select "KV_CONFIGS" from the dropdown.
    -   Verify table populates with data (mocked or real).
3.  **Editing**:
    -   Click "Edit" on a row.
    -   Change the value.
    -   Save.
    -   Verify the update persists (refresh or check backend).
4.  **Error Handling**:
    -   Try invalid JSON.
    -   Verify error message.
